					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/leicontis" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(393373); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=393373&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610204982" alt="Leicontis" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=393373)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/leicontis" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(393373); return false;" >Leicontis</a></span> <span class="odate time_1269287080 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">22 Mar 2010 19:44</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-731404">
									

<p>I know that this wiki was born in some fashion or another out of postings on /x/, but if there's a more detailed history out there I haven't found it yet. What I'd like to do is ask those who have been around a longer time than newbies like me for a little informal history of the SCPF wiki. I'm not asking for you to post some big, long, detailed history - just if and when you feel like it, drop a story into this thread or onto a new page. Something like a quick description of the site's birth, or of some of its growing pains. There are incidents and former members that get referenced by long-timers that tend to be lost on us newbies unless they're explained, and I suspect it gets old retyping the stories in chat time after time.</p>
<p>For example, I've heard that before the current strictly-not-a-roleplaying-site policy, things got pretty messy and confusing in places, and that there was one particular user that exemplified the problem. Since most and/or all traces of that trouble have been cleaned up, it would be interesting (and possibly amusing and/or cringe-inducing) to hear more about it.</p>
<p>So, is there any particular period/event/former user that stands out to you as particularly influential (either as a good role model or as something that must never, in the name of all that is good and pure, be repeated)? Any fun or interesting story you'd like to share of earlier times? Even just some nugget of wisdom you've gleaned through your greater experience that doesn't really fit anywhere else? <span style="text-decoration: line-through;">I'm</span> We're all <span style="text-decoration: line-through;">ears</span> eyes!</p>

							</div>

								
