																		A timeline of the SCP project according to Ghost
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/a-fat-ghost" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(173799); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=173799&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610204982" alt="A Fat Ghost" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=173799)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/a-fat-ghost" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(173799); return false;" >A Fat Ghost</a></span> <span class="odate time_1269305445 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">23 Mar 2010 00:50</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-731676">
									

<p>I know you haven't asked for a long story, but I'm giving you one anyway before I forget all the details. I'm leaving out usernames to avoid offending, flattering, or otherwise upsetting any of the readers at home.</p>
<p>(Late) Summer, 2007 (I had earlier though it to be spring, archived records of the old wiki have corrected me on this)<br />
-SCP-173 is posted on 4chan's /x/, it is met with consternation and curiosity. The thread lingers for days, with anonymii seeming to approve of the concept.<br />
-For the next few months, SCP-173 is reposted several times, and new threads spring from these reposts into the first of what would be the main Series list. The articles are either submitted as whole drafts, or put together and edited in pieces by various (still anonymous) users.</p>
<p>January (19), 2008 to June 2008<br />
-The SCP Wiki on editthis.info goes up, the articles constructed so far are quickly posted to it.<br />
-For the next few months, users swarm the wiki, linked from /x/, /b/, and other 4chan boards (possibly 7chan as well), reading, editing, and creating new articles. The total number of articles jumps from about a dozen to one hundred sixty-six (including twelve joke articles).</p>
<p>(Mid) June, 2008 and onward<br />
-the site can no longer be hosted on editthis due to changing policy, and an alternative is found in Wikidot. The existing articles are transferred over, with the help of several of the more prominent users of the old site. Most of these users formed the new site's first administration team, many of whom still remain (if not necessarily in an administrative role).<br />
-a spree of article vandalism occurs during the night, dealt with mainly by a small group of users headed by a heroic individual who shall not be named here. This causes the site staff to consider security measure for the site.<br />
-over the next few months, the site undergoes changes to prevent damage to the SCP Series, including a larger administration team, and several (they didn't all pan out so well) methods of screening new members for what is now a wiki closed to anonymous edits.</p>
<p>This is a rough timeline, and I expect to have missed a lot, but this is basically the backbone of the project's history as far as I've witnessed.</p>

