			<div class="content" id="post-content-731690">
									

<p>well, let me think a bit…</p>
<p>Honestly, while I'm one of the most productive of the users, I'm not the oldest. I think that goes to A Fat Ghost, at least as far as "oldest active member" goes. Still, I did manage to hop in on the ground floor of this, if not the basement.</p>
<p>It all started with SCP-173. It was a random, one-off creepypasta, but it inspired a lot of people. before long, other entries started popping up, and then one day someone made a wiki for it, so they wouldn't all 404 eventually. This was when /x/ was still young-ish, and The Holders, Ted the Caver, Treedog, and other old-school /x/ rubbish was still very new and decent.</p>
<p>My first entry was SCP-882, and it was shockingly well received. Went on a writing binge, making about 1-2 entries a day for a week. Finally, I got the courage to join the first wiki, and started posting my stuff directly to there. Things were VERY primitive then, basically a Wikipedia clone, no real forum, ratings, discussion…it was hard. still, we kept plugging away at it, and before long a very hazy coalition started to form, a vague underlying hint of some massive force moving in the shadows, editing reality for the good of the masses.</p>
<p>I met a lot of the older users at this point…most of which are now, sadly, inactive. Kain sticks out in my memory…mainly because I though his username was pretentious rubbish, and I disliked Able…but over time, I realized more and more some of the undercurrents and hints he was trying to get across, and started to warm up. That, or I realized he was a very cool, fun guy and just got over it. One of the two.</p>
<p>It was somewhere at this point that the term "Foundation" came in to use. I honestly think I suggested it first, but it's more likely I was just a staunch supporter. With the name came a more concrete identity, and we went from "The SCP Series" to "The Foundation".</p>
<p>In time, we outgrew the old wiki, and needed to move to greener pastures. I think it was Kain who suggested the move, or possibly Kondraki, but I'm honestly not sure. Anyway, we shifted everything, and somehow in the shuffle I became a admin…mainly because I wrote a lot, I think. It was a mess for a few days, but in time we had things set up semi-ok, and it look like smooth sailing…</p>
<p>Until Hagger.</p>
<p>to be continued…both for dramatic effect, and because these are big posts.</p>

