														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-731701">
									

<p>Haggar was a hacker, and hit us twice. The first caught us totally off guard, and had us reeling for a while. The second was really bad, but was fought off by the near-constant anti-attrition of a few users. I, at best, threw rocks when my connection was stable, but this was a very cool moment when people showed this poor little wiki was worth defending.</p>
<p>After that, things got calmer. Clef, Bright, and others joined up. We played around with stories, community projects, and other random ideas for a while. Then we had to deal with Dr. L. Dr. L was a 12-14 year old fanboy who was…not good. Example: In one of his stories, SCP-682 speaks in Shakespearean english. Bad Shakespearean english. He was our first banning outside of vandals, and showed that, just maybe, our somewhat silly and in-joke character profiles were sending the wrong message.</p>
<p>Most recently, we've tried to tone down the "wacky adventures" ideas, and tried to show some of the more grim, unsettling aspects of The Foundation and the world around it. Not to say humor is gone, but a better integration of it is being found.</p>
<p>Honestly, most of the incidents since moving here are tolerably well documented. We've had bad users, trolls, porn, steel-winged Indians, white-tailed superhero rapist-killing catboys, vomiting eyeballs, and a naked girl in a lab coat. I love this place. The people, the stories, everything.</p>
<p>That's…err…really it, I guess. If you want more specific incidents, just ask…</p>

