														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-731835">
									

<p>And in the middle of all that, I joined up, and slowly but surely finagled my way into the upper ranks, largely by being an asshole with ideas.</p>
<p>We've had two mass edits, the second of which actually worked. Hopefully, we won't ever do another one, cause frankly, they suck.</p>
<p>We've enacted only two permanent site bans, of actual users, Unconfirmed_reptile for being 12, (Side note, although we do not have an official age limit, I tend to deny any applicants under the age of 14, not because I don't think they couldn't be good, but because as a guy growing older, I don't want to expose kids not in high school to some of the shit on this site) and LBD, who <em>just didn't get it</em>.</p>
<p>One of the things thats changed on this site is accountability. For a long time we were just open, any anonymous could do anything. We've really tightened up, and in my opinion, it's worked. Also, within the past six… seven months? God, more? we've changed to an actual application process, changing questions once a week, to try and prevent some of the really godawful articles.</p>
<p>On the note of applications, about half the people who apply get approved. Of those denied, more then 3/4 are denied because they don't do step 4 or 5. Hence, my usual rants about that. We really can;t make the process any easier.</p>

