				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/pair-of-ducks" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(172939); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=172939&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610204982" alt="Pair Of Ducks" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=172939)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/pair-of-ducks" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(172939); return false;" >Pair Of Ducks</a></span> <span class="odate time_1269309183 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">23 Mar 2010 01:53</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-731737">
									

<p>I found the SCP wiki whilst searching for a porn site. Not kidding.</p>
<p>This was back in June or July of 2008, on the edit.this wiki. I lurked there for a while, and I finally joined the site itself in August when we had moved here to wikidot. I was an avid lurker, but not very involved in the community.</p>
<p>I didn't really become involved until October. October was an important month for us, really. Kondraki, Clef, Bright, Fishmonger, Iceberg, Gerald … they all joined the site in October 08.</p>
<p>I became active in the community because of the chat. I twas actually Kondraki that originally made #site19, actually. But chat was fairly ignored then; only him, myself, snorlison, and Fritz (yes, Fritz!) were ever on. Chat was also supposed to be in-character back then!</p>
<p>Eventually #site19 become completely forgotten … but I came back, registered it, and started really trying to get people in there. For a while, it was -still- mostly myself, Kondraki, and Snorlison on … I remember when Gears came into the room one day, it was like we'd met a celebrity xD … but chat got big pretty quick; soon we had Iceberg, Rights, and others popping in regularly.</p>
<p>I like to think of all this as the "Gears/Kain Power Duo" Era, because even though The Admin was around, they were the ones trying to get everything settled. It was rather amusing watching them work, because though they were both very nice guys they definitely had very different ideas about what they liked for the site.</p>
<p>After this, we tumbled flailing and screaming into what I like to think of as the "Kondraki" Era.</p>
<p>The "Kondraki Era" you have to admit, was probably one of the best for the wiki. A lot of new content, a lot of new users, and a lot of enthusiasm and productivity. We had a growing community, but it was small enough that everyone knew everyone, and everyone could keep track of all the new articles as they were put up. Up until then everything had been very chaotic and very 'anything goes' … which was arguably a good thing to some degree, but during this time we had a lot of things solidify, and we started worrying about "canon". Stories started going up. We started raising the bar on quality.</p>
<p>After this, well, things became a bit more difficult. Gone were the days of freedom and enthusiasm, and it really started to hit all the senior members that "SHIT, we've got work to do". We had articles to review, a growing and unruly member-base to keep track of and discipline. A lot of the "Guides" started going up. Before this, if you wanted to write an SCP, you were supposed to -read all of them- and get the general idea on how to do things. But some of the articles we were getting meant we obviously needed to hold people's hands a bit better. Kondraki started being problematic then … as a result, a lot of the administrative pull shifted from Kondraki to Gears again, as well as Clef.</p>
<p>My memory gets fuzzy here, and I probably have a few things out of order as it is.</p>

							</div>

								
					
