			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-731832">
									

<p>It were about that point last march when I showed up. Kon was at his peak, Gears and Clef were tearing the main list <em>down</em> with some well written articles, and the influx of newbies was heavy enough to let me slip in under the radar without being banned before I could get my shit together. Those were the days in 19 of mass kicks and lulzbans, of goofy shit and rainbow spam, and I owe a special debt of gratitude to a terrible /b/tard called "D" for always being that significant bit worse a n00b than I was. I don't imagine I'd have lasted long otherwise.</p>
<p>Gerald had beaten me here by a bit, and Bouncl and Light both showed up either on my heels or just before, depending on who's telling the story. The reign of ghengis Kon was winding down, and kids were getting dissatisfied with being kickspammed every ten minutes. Changes were in the works. It was the best of times, it was the worst of times. It was the timeliest of times. Of all the offices in the world, she had to walk into mine. But I digress.</p>
<p>Anyway, since I've been here, I've had the privelige of watching the focus of the site shift and a clearer, more defined set of goals come into play. As one of the first of the new generation of users, I missed the party on things like wacky decommissions and the like. Instead, we had to deal with vibrating bondage men and LBD and baby hitler and the slow mental degredation of an established user into a raging troll. Good times were had all around.</p>

