														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-732387">
									

<p>Hey, I don't think anybody's complaining about the end result - a bunch of cool and amusing stories that also mock poorly-written articles, almost in the style of "Protectors of the Plot Continuum". The lead researchers are larger than life, sure, but an organization staffed solely by normal people wouldn't last long against the abnormalities of SCPs. I wouldn't call any of them Mary Sues (except, if I'm honest with myself, Kondraki a la Duke till Dawn, though that has the redeeming quality of being hilarious), especially since often at their most OTT when it's least relevant and most amusing. As far as Dr. Clef (potentially - his claims about himself seem like Heath Ledger's Joker's explanations of his scars) being the devil, think of what it says about the Foundation that they'd contain God but bring Satan on staff in a position of authority.</p>

							</div>

								
					
